## AtlasIT Platform QA — Full System Evaluation (End-to-End)

Scope: `/console` + all navigable modules from current session
Method: Functional + structural + compliance + product integrity validation
Assumption: Single-tenant demo state with partial backend wiring

---

# 1. Global Platform Findings (Cross-Cutting)

### Critical Systemic Issues (P0)

| Area           | Issue                                           | Impact                                 | Fix Strategy                                          |
| -------------- | ----------------------------------------------- | -------------------------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------- |
| Auth           | Console auth bypass flag still implied          | Full platform exposure risk            | Enforce Cloudflare Access + JWT validation middleware |
| Data Integrity | Majority of metrics appear static/demo          | Breaks trust + unusable for compliance | Wire D1 → UI with strict schema validation            |
| Evidence Chain | No immutable linkage between actions → evidence | Fails SOC2/HIPAA auditability          | Enforce R2 write + hash per workflow step             |
| API Parity     | UI renders features not backed by APIs          | Silent failure risk                    | CI check: OpenAPI vs route handlers                   |
| Multi-Tenancy  | No visible tenant isolation guarantees          | Data leakage risk                      | Enforce tenant_id in every query + policy guard       |
| Observability  | No visible logs, traces, or failure states      | No debugging or SLO enforcement        | Add OpenTelemetry + structured logs                   |

